Having played the story from start to finish without DLC, I must say that the game deserves a "neutral" review, but since that's not possible, I don't recommend because:

* Multiple times it feels like the game is wasting your time (and it is);
* The resources and recipes seem unbalanced, so you end up with too many of an item with no use while trying to get the one you want;
* You can't sell most things which aggravates the previous problem;
* There are still bugs in the game, even though they're not game-breaking;
* The vanilla game has some misleading tooltips and item descriptions;
* There are several instances of things that clearly meant to be more, but remained like an unfinished part of the game;
* The game is very constricted in a small area that doesn't feel "alive";

Having said that, it still can be fun when you what you have to do.

